@REM --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE About "What is the HCMenu editor all about?"
Before answering this question it's better to answer this question:
"What is the Haute-Cuisine Menu?"
Simplysaid: The HCMenu is a programm which turns a simple textfile into
a menu. This menu is a fully cofigurable window containing a number of
items. Each item may be selected (activated) by a simple mousclick.

As already stated, the menu works with a textfile. With the help of a
standard texteditor like "Cygnus Ed" or the terrifying "Ed" from the
workbech disk is is possible to add items etc. to a menu or make a
complete new menu.
That is not hard to do, but there are more simpler ways to maintain
a menu. And that is the reason I coded the HCMenuEditor. It's a tool
which enables the user to maintain his menus with the mouse, since
that is what the Amiga makes great...
@ENDNODE

